Investment returns: Constant Sharpe Ratio, DC equal to implied geom mean

High standard deviations (risks) are associated with high returns. DC is set to ir.mean - ir.sd^2/2. All plans start with the same asset value.

Benefit:

1: No COLA; 2: 2% COLA
